UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff—Appellee, v. Shaquan Jermaine WINNS, Defendant—Appellant. No. 08-7185. United States Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. Submitted: Nov. 13, 2008. Decided: Nov. 20, 2008. Shaquan Jermaine Winns, Appellant Pro Se. Eric Matthew Hurt, Assistant United States Attorney, Newport News, Virginia, for Appellee.

Before WILKINSON, NIEMEYER, and SHEDD, Circuit Judges.

Affirmed by unpublished PER CURIAM opinion.

Unpublished opinions are not binding precedent in this circuit.

PER CURIAM:

Shaquan Winns appeals the district court’s order denying his 18 U.S.C. § 3582(c) (2006) motion. We have reviewed the record and find no reversible error. Accordingly, we affirm for the reasons stated by the district court. United States v. Winns, No. 4:05-cr-00097-RBS-FBS-1 (E.D.Va. May 16, 2008). We dispense with oral argument because the facts and legal contentions are adequately presented in the materials before the court and argument would not aid the decisional process.

AFFIRMED.
